<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: direct_stratum_component_join_implementation
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Interconnect_module_connection_routing_mim.direct_stratum_component_join_implementation">
A <b>direct_stratum_component_join_implementation</b> is a  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship"/> that implements the
ARM concept of <express_ref linkend="Interconnect_module_connection_routing:arm:Interconnect_module_connection_routing_arm.Direct_stratum_component_join_implementation"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: direct_stratum_component_join_implementation.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Interconnect_module_connection_routing_mim.direct_stratum_component_join_implementation.wr:WR1">
The <b>direct_stratum_component_join_implementation</b> shall not
participate in a complex instance with other than the  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship"/> supertype.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: indirect_stratum_component_join_implementation
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Interconnect_module_connection_routing_mim.indirect_stratum_component_join_implementation">
An <b>indirect_stratum_component_join_implementation</b> is a  <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:mim:Layered_interconnect_module_design_mim.plated_inter_stratum_feature"/> that implements the
ARM concept <express_ref linkend="Interconnect_module_connection_routing:arm:Interconnect_module_connection_routing_arm.Indirect_stratum_component_join_implementation"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Rule: junction_vertex_allocation_constraint
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Interconnect_module_connection_routing_mim.junction_vertex_allocation_constraint">
<note> This rule may not have been updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

The <b>junction_vertex_allocation_constraint</b> rule constrains the related and
relating  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> of a  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship"/> when it is a junction
vertex allocation.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: junction_vertex_allocation_constraint.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Interconnect_module_connection_routing_mim.junction_vertex_allocation_constraint.wr:WR1">
IF  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship"/>.name = 'junction vertex allocation' THEN 
SELF.related_shape_aspect shall be 
(a  <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:mim:Layered_interconnect_module_design_mim.layer_connection_point"/>\ <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/>.description = 'explicitly located') 
(a  <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:mim:Layered_interconnect_module_design_mim.join_shape_aspect"/>\ <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/>.name = 'inter stratum join').
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: junction_vertex_allocation_constraint.WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Interconnect_module_connection_routing_mim.junction_vertex_allocation_constraint.wr:WR2">
IF  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship"/>.name = 'junction vertex allocation' THEN 
SELF.relating_shape_aspect shall have a description = 'topological junction'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Rule: junction_vertex_allocation_unique_constraint
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Interconnect_module_connection_routing_mim.junction_vertex_allocation_unique_constraint">
<note> This rule may not have been updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

The <b>junction_vertex_allocation_unique_constraint</b> rule constrains the
 <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship"/> population members, that fill the role of
ARM junction_vertex_allocation, so that the ARM required_vertex
attribute shall be unique within the population.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: junction_vertex_allocation_unique_constraint.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Interconnect_module_connection_routing_mim.junction_vertex_allocation_unique_constraint.wr:WR1">
Every instance of  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship"/> with a name of
'junction vertex allocation' must have a unique  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> entity
with a name of 'topological junction' as the  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship"/>'s
relating_shape_aspect attribute.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Rule: physical_connectivity_abstraction_map_unique_constraint
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Interconnect_module_connection_routing_mim.physical_connectivity_abstraction_map_unique_constraint">
<note> This rule may not have been updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

The <b>physical_connectivity_abstraction_map_unique_constraint</b> rule constrains the
 <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship"/> population members, that fill the role of ARM
physical_connectivity_abstraction_map, to have unique ARM geometric_context_based_definition
attributes with each ARM name_space_context_based_definition attribute.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: physical_connectivity_abstraction_map_unique_constraint.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Interconnect_module_connection_routing_mim.physical_connectivity_abstraction_map_unique_constraint.wr:WR1">
Every instance of  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship"/> with a name of
'physical to topological abstraction map' that references a common
 <express_ref linkend="Functional_design_elaboration:mim:Functional_design_elaboration_mim.physical_connectivity_element"/> must reference a unique  <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:mim:Physical_unit_design_view_mim.component_shape_aspect"/>
with a description of either 'conductive interconnect element with pre defined transitions'
or 'conductive interconnect element with user defined single transition'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Rule: topological_junction_unique_constraint
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Interconnect_module_connection_routing_mim.topological_junction_unique_constraint">
<note> This rule may not have been updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

The <b>topological_junction_unique_constraint</b> rule constrains the  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> population members, that
fill the role of ARM topological_junction, to have unique names on each scope.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: topological_junction_unique_constraint.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Interconnect_module_connection_routing_mim.topological_junction_unique_constraint.wr:WR1">
Every instance of  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> with a description of 'topological junction' that
is referenced by a  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect_relationship"/> with a name of 'topological junction scope'
that references a common  <express_ref linkend="Functional_design_elaboration:mim:Functional_design_elaboration_mim.physical_connectivity_definition"/> must have a unique name
attribute value.
</ext_description>

</ext_descriptions>
